BY EMMANUEL MGBEAHURUIKE, Owerri Imo State Government has restated its determination and commitment to provide an enabling environment for the organized private sector to contribute their quota towards the development of the state in line with its shared prosperity agenda. The special Adviser to the Governor on Bureau and Local Government Affairs, Hon. Rubby Emele who gave the reassurance while interacting with newsmen in Owerri, stressed that Senator Hope Uzodinma led administration is irrevocably committed to re-launch the state on the path of progress and sustainable development for socio-economic development of the state and South East zone. The Special Adviser noted that despite the raging Covid-19 pandemic which confronted the administration at inception, it had been able to manage the disturbing situation through necessary administrative mechanisms, including adequate sensitization of the masses on relevant established protocols and safety guidelines. Hon. Emele a former local government chairman explained that the state government is set to reposition the state as the economic hub of the South East. According to her, Governor Uzodimma is working tirelessly towards reinvigorating the socio-economic road map of the state so as to position the state for elevated sustainable development. Apart from addressing the challenges of some health institutions in the Local Government Councils, the Hon. Emele highlighted that Senator Uzodimma administration had equally provided well equipped mobile clinics to accelerate the pace of health care delivery system in the state, just as it has revamped the state water scheme for regular supply of potable water for the populace. Hon. Emele who also spoke of government’s efforts to revive and to resuscitate all moribund industries in the state, to support the administration to enable the state move forward in growth, development and transformation. 